import { useState } from 'react'; import { Link } from 'react-router-dom'; function UserProfile() { const [isEditing, setIsEditing] = useState(false); // Simplified user data structure const [userData, setUserData] = useState({ name: "Alex Johnson", username: "alexj2025", picture: "https://placeholder.com/150", traits: { openToRoommates: true, budget: 1000, leaseDuration: 6, smoking: false, drinking: true, housingPreference: 'multiple' // or 'single' } }); const handleTraitChange = (trait, value) => { setUserData(prev => ({ ...prev, traits: { ...prev.traits, [trait]: value } })); }; const ProfileView = () => (
{/* Basic Information */}

Profile Information

Name

{userData.name}

Username

{userData.username}

{/* Preferences */}

Preferences

Open to Roommates

{userData.traits.openToRoommates ? 'Yes' : 'No'}

Monthly Budget

${userData.traits.budget}

Lease Duration

{userData.traits.leaseDuration} months

Housing Preference

{userData.traits.housingPreference === 'multiple' ? 'Multiple Gender Housing' : 'Single Gender Housing'}

Smoking

{userData.traits.smoking ? 'Yes' : 'No'}

Drinking

{userData.traits.drinking ? 'Yes' : 'No'}

); return (
{/* Header section remains similar but simplified */}
Back to Home
{isEditing ? ( <>

Edit Profile

{/* Existing edit form content */}
{/* Basic Information */}
setUserData({...userData, name: e.target.value})} className="w-full px-3 py-2 border border-gray-300 rounded-md" />
setUserData({...userData, username: e.target.value})} className="w-full px-3 py-2 border border-gray-300 rounded-md" />
{/* Traits Section */}

Preferences

handleTraitChange('openToRoommates', e.target.checked)} className="mr-2" />
handleTraitChange('budget', parseInt(e.target.value))} className="w-full" /> ${userData.traits.budget}
handleTraitChange('leaseDuration', parseInt(e.target.value))} className="w-full" /> {userData.traits.leaseDuration} months
handleTraitChange('smoking', e.target.checked)} className="mr-2" />
handleTraitChange('drinking', e.target.checked)} className="mr-2" />
) : ( )}
); } export default UserProfile;
